Decision Trees and Random Forest

This file implements Decision Tree and Random Forest models for classification.

Builds a decision tree to learn patterns from data using feature splits
Extends to a random forest by combining multiple trees for improved accuracy and robustness
Compares model performance and predictions
Output
Predicted labels for the dataset
Improved generalization using ensemble learning (Random Forest over single tree)
Key Idea

Decision Trees learn simple rules from data, while Random Forest reduces overfitting by averaging multiple trees.
